==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maxilla
<hw>Max*il"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Maxillae</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., dim. of
<ets>mala</ets> jaw, jawbone.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The bone of either the upper or the under jaw.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The bone, or principal bone, of the upper jaw, the
bone of the lower jaw being the <xex>mandible</xex>.</def> <mark>[Now
commonly used in this restricted sense.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the lower or outer jaws of
arthropods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ There are usually two pairs in Crustacea and one pair in
insects. In certain insects they are not used as jaws, but may form
suctorial organs. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under <er>Lepidoptera</er>, and
<er>Diptera</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 904 --></p>

<p><ent>Maxillary</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Maxillar</ent>⟦br⟧
